029/**
030 * Serializes POJO models to URL-encoded notation with UON-encoded values (a notation for URL-encoded query paramter values).
031 *
032 * <h5 class='section'>Media types:</h5>
033 * <p>
034 * Handles <c>Accept</c> types:  <bc>application/x-www-form-urlencoded</bc>
035 * <p>
036 * Produces <c>Content-Type</c> types:  <bc>application/x-www-form-urlencoded</bc>
037 *
038 * <h5 class='topic'>Description</h5>
039 *
040 * This serializer provides several serialization options.
041 * <br>Typically, one of the predefined DEFAULT serializers will be sufficient.
042 * <br>However, custom serializers can be constructed to fine-tune behavior.
043 *
044 * <p>
045 * The following shows a sample object defined in Javascript:
046 * <p class='bjson'>
047 *    {
048 *       id: 1,
049 *       name: <js>'John Smith'</js>,
050 *       uri: <js>'http://sample/addressBook/person/1'</js>,
051 *       addressBookUri: <js>'http://sample/addressBook'</js>,
052 *       birthDate: <js>'1946-08-12T00:00:00Z'</js>,
053 *       otherIds: <jk>null</jk>,
054 *       addresses: [
055 *          {
056 *             uri: <js>'http://sample/addressBook/address/1'</js>,
057 *             personUri: <js>'http://sample/addressBook/person/1'</js>,
058 *             id: 1,
059 *             street: <js>'100 Main Street'</js>,
060 *             city: <js>'Anywhereville'</js>,
061 *             state: <js>'NY'</js>,
062 *             zip: 12345,
063 *             isCurrent: <jk>true</jk>,
064 *          }
065 *       ]
066 *    }
067 * </p>
068 *
069 * <p>
070 * Using the "strict" syntax defined in this document, the equivalent URL-encoded notation would be as follows:
071 * <p class='burlenc'>
072 *    <ua>id</ua>=<un>1</un>
073 *    &amp;<ua>name</ua>=<us>'John+Smith'</us>,
074 *    &amp;<ua>uri</ua>=<us>http://sample/addressBook/person/1</us>,
075 *    &amp;<ua>addressBookUri</ua>=<us>http://sample/addressBook</us>,
076 *    &amp;<ua>birthDate</ua>=<us>1946-08-12T00:00:00Z</us>,
077 *    &amp;<ua>otherIds</ua>=<uk>null</uk>,
078 *    &amp;<ua>addresses</ua>=@(
079 *       (
080 *          <ua>uri</ua>=<us>http://sample/addressBook/address/1</us>,
081 *          <ua>personUri</ua>=<us>http://sample/addressBook/person/1</us>,
082 *          <ua>id</ua>=<un>1</un>,
083 *          <ua>street</ua>=<us>'100+Main+Street'</us>,
084 *          <ua>city</ua>=<us>Anywhereville</us>,
085 *          <ua>state</ua>=<us>NY</us>,
086 *          <ua>zip</ua>=<un>12345</un>,
087 *          <ua>isCurrent</ua>=<uk>true</uk>
088 *       )
089 *    )
090 * </p>
091 *
092 * <h5 class='section'>Example:</h5>
093 * <p class='bjava'>
094 *    <jc>// Serialize a Map</jc>
095 *    Map <jv>map</jv> = JsonMap.<jsm>ofJson</jsm>(<js>"{a:'b',c:1,d:false,e:['f',1,false],g:{h:'i'}}"</js>);
096 *
097 *    <jc>// Serialize to value equivalent to JSON.</jc>
098 *    <jc>// Produces "a=b&amp;c=1&amp;d=false&amp;e=@(f,1,false)&amp;g=(h=i)"</jc>
099 *    String <jv>uenc</jv> = UrlEncodingSerializer.<jsf>DEFAULT</jsf>.serialize(<jv>map</jv>);
100 *
101 *    <jc>// Serialize a bean</jc>
102 *    <jk>public class</jk> Person {
103 *       <jk>public</jk> Person(String <jv>name</jv>);
104 *       <jk>public</jk> String getName();
105 *       <jk>public int</jk> getAge();
106 *       <jk>public</jk> Address getAddress();
107 *       <jk>public boolean</jk> deceased;
108 *    }
109 *
110 *    <jk>public class</jk> Address {
111 *       <jk>public</jk> String getStreet();
112 *       <jk>public</jk> String getCity();
113 *       <jk>public</jk> String getState();
114 *       <jk>public int</jk> getZip();
115 *    }
116 *
117 *    Person <jv>person</jv> = <jk>new</jk> Person(<js>"John Doe"</js>, 23, <js>"123 Main St"</js>, <js>"Anywhere"</js>, <js>"NY"</js>, 12345, <jk>false</jk>);
118 *
119 *    <jc>// Produces "name=John+Doe&amp;age=23&amp;address=(street='123+Main+St',city=Anywhere,state=NY,zip=12345)&amp;deceased=false"</jc>
120 *    String <jv>uenc</jv> = UrlEncodingSerializer.<jsf>DEFAULT</jsf>.serialize(<jv>person</jv>);
121 * </p>
122 *
123 * <h5 class='section'>Notes:</h5><ul>
124 *    <li class='note'>This class is thread safe and reusable.
125 * </ul>
126 *
127 * <h5 class='section'>See Also:</h5><ul>
128 *    <li class='link'><a class="doclink" href="https://juneau.apache.org/docs/topics/UrlEncodingBasics">URL-Encoding Basics</a>
129 * </ul>
130 */
131public class UrlEncodingSerializer extends UonSerializer implements UrlEncodingMetaProvider {

211   /**
212    * Builder class.
213    */
214   @FluentSetters
215   public static class Builder extends UonSerializer.Builder {
216
217      private static final Cache<HashKey,UrlEncodingSerializer> CACHE = Cache.of(HashKey.class, UrlEncodingSerializer.class).build();
218
219      boolean expandedParams;
220
221      /**
222       * Constructor, default settings.
223       */
224      protected Builder() {
225         produces("application/x-www-form-urlencoded");
226         expandedParams = env("UrlEncoding.expandedParams", false);
227      }
228
229      /**
230       * Copy constructor.
231       *
232       * @param copyFrom The bean to copy from.
233       */
234      protected Builder(UrlEncodingSerializer copyFrom) {
235         super(copyFrom);
236         expandedParams = copyFrom.expandedParams;
237      }
238
239      /**
240       * Copy constructor.
241       *
242       * @param copyFrom The builder to copy from.
243       */
244      protected Builder(Builder copyFrom) {
245         super(copyFrom);
246         expandedParams = copyFrom.expandedParams;
247      }
248
249      @Override /* Context.Builder */
250      public Builder copy() {
251         return new Builder(this);
252      }
253
254      @Override /* Context.Builder */
255      public UrlEncodingSerializer build() {
256         return cache(CACHE).build(UrlEncodingSerializer.class);
257      }
258
259      @Override /* Context.Builder */
260      public HashKey hashKey() {
261         return HashKey.of(
262            super.hashKey(),
263            expandedParams
264         );
265      }

268      // Properties

270
271      /**
272       * Serialize bean property collections/arrays as separate key/value pairs.
273       *
274       * <p>
275       * By default, serializing the array <c>[1,2,3]</c> results in <c>?key=$a(1,2,3)</c>.
276       * <br>When enabled, serializing the same array results in <c>?key=1&amp;key=2&amp;key=3</c>.
277       *
278       * <p>
279       * This option only applies to beans.
280       *
281       * <h5 class='section'>Notes:</h5><ul>
282       *    <li class='note'>
283       *       If parsing multi-part parameters, it's highly recommended to use <c>Collections</c> or <c>Lists</c>
284       *       as bean property types instead of arrays since arrays have to be recreated from scratch every time a value
285       *       is added to it.
286       * </ul>
287       *
288       * <h5 class='section'>Example:</h5>
289       * <p class='bjava'>
290       *    <jc>// A sample bean.</jc>
291       *    <jk>public class</jk> A {
292       *       <jk>public</jk> String[] <jf>f1</jf> = {<js>"a"</js>,<js>"b"</js>};
293       *       <jk>public</jk> List&lt;String&gt; <jf>f2</jf> = Arrays.<jsm>asList</jsm>(<jk>new</jk> String[]{<js>"c"</js>,<js>"d"</js>});
294       *    }
295       *
296       *    <jc>// Normal serializer.</jc>
297       *    WriterSerializer <jv>serializer1</jv> = UrlEncodingSerializer.<jsf>DEFAULT</jsf>;
298       *
299       *    <jc>// Expanded-params serializer.</jc>
300       *    WriterSerializer <jv>serializer2</jv> = UrlEncodingSerializer.<jsm>create</jsm>().expandedParams().build();
301       *
302       *  <jc>// Produces "f1=(a,b)&amp;f2=(c,d)"</jc>
303       *    String <jv>out1</jv> = <jv>serializer1</jv>.serialize(<jk>new</jk> A());
304       *
305       *    <jc>// Produces "f1=a&amp;f1=b&amp;f2=c&amp;f2=d"</jc>
306       *    String <jv>out2</jv> = <jv>serializer2</jv>.serialize(<jk>new</jk> A());
307       * </p>
308       *
309       * @return This object.
310       */
311      @FluentSetter
312      public Builder expandedParams() {
313         return expandedParams(true);
314      }
315
316      /**
317       * Same as {@link #expandedParams()} but allows you to explicitly specify the value.
318       *
319       * @param value The value for this setting.
320       * @return This object.
321       */
322      @FluentSetter
323      public Builder expandedParams(boolean value) {
324         expandedParams = value;
325         return this;
326      }

1050   @Override /* UrlEncodingMetaProvider */
1051   public UrlEncodingClassMeta getUrlEncodingClassMeta(ClassMeta<?> cm) {
1052      UrlEncodingClassMeta m = urlEncodingClassMetas.get(cm);
1053      if (m == null) {
1054         m = new UrlEncodingClassMeta(cm, this);
1055         urlEncodingClassMetas.put(cm, m);
1056      }
1057      return m;
1058   }
1059
1060   @Override /* UrlEncodingMetaProvider */
1061   public UrlEncodingBeanPropertyMeta getUrlEncodingBeanPropertyMeta(BeanPropertyMeta bpm) {
1062      if (bpm == null)
1063         return UrlEncodingBeanPropertyMeta.DEFAULT;
1064      UrlEncodingBeanPropertyMeta m = urlEncodingBeanPropertyMetas.get(bpm);
1065      if (m == null) {
1066         m = new UrlEncodingBeanPropertyMeta(bpm.getDelegateFor(), this);
1067         urlEncodingBeanPropertyMetas.put(bpm, m);
1068      }
1069      return m;
1070   }

1079    * @see Builder#expandedParams()
